{"questionId":"14079","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a right triangle ABC. Point D lies on AB such that CD&nbsp;bisects AĈB.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/9458b833ab138b0d6ccd877fdee6a3dbab62da86.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">AĈD = <em>θ</em> and AC = 14 cm</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence or otherwise, find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{BC}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>BC</mtext> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct working &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</em> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{7}{{25}} = \\frac{{14}}{{{\\text{BC}}}}\"> <mfrac> <mn>7</mn> <mrow> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>14</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>BC</mtext> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{BC}} = \\frac{{14 \\times 25}}{7}\"> <mrow> <mtext>BC</mtext> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>14</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> <mn>7</mn> </mfrac> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{BC}} = 50\"> <mrow> <mtext>BC</mtext> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>50</mn> </math></span> (cm)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14079","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.S_3c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence or otherwise, find BC .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geome